📖 Surah Al-Anbiya (21:107) 

🌺 Tilawat
وَمَا أَرْسَلْنَاكَ إِلَّا رَحْمَةً لِّلْعَالَمِينَ

🌺 Roman Urdu
“Wa maa arsalnaaka illa rahmatan lil ‘aalameen.”

🌺 Translation
“Aur (ai Nabi ﷺ) humne aapko tamaam jahanon ke liye rehmat hi bana kar bheja hai.”

✨ Key Points for Explanation :-

1. Nabi ﷺ ki Bhejne ka Maqsad

Allah ne Nabi ﷺ ko sirf ek qom ya ek zamane ke liye nahi bheja.
Aap ﷺ ka paigham poore insaaniyat, jinn aur sab makhlooq ke liye hai.
Ye Islam ki universality ko show karta hai.

2. Rehmat ka Matlab

Guidance: Qur’an laye jo hidayat hai.
Forgiveness: Dushmanon ko bhi maaf kiya.
Kindness: Yateemon, ghareebon, aur aurton ko izzat di.
Justice: Mazloomon ka saath diya aur zulm khatam kiya.

3. Examples of Rahmat from Seerah

Fath Makkah ke waqt → Dushmanon ko maaf kar diya, kaha: “Aaj tum sab ke liye maafi hai.”
Ghulamon ko azaad karne ki hidayat di.
Animals aur environment ke liye bhi rahmat: unnecessary torture se mana kiya.

4. Lessons for Us 

Islam sirf humein nahi, poore society ke liye rahmat banne ki dawat deta hai.
Hum apne akhlaq aur adaab se dusron ko Islam ki khubsurti dikhayen.
Humari dawat aur kaam me softness, kindness aur sabr hona chahiye.
Har shakhs ke liye ek chhoti si “rahmat” banna hi Nabi ﷺ ki sunnat ko follow karna hai.

🌷 Reflection Question (For Discussion)

“Main apne ghar, doston aur society ke andar rahmat ka zariya kaise ban sakti hoon?”
